<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-11-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="214" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-11-13"><hi rend="italic">November 13,
                                    1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 249.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that in
                            accordance with the constitutional provision the Belgian Parliament
                            convened on the second Tuesday of November.</p>
                        <pb facs="0963" n="813" xml:id="pg_813"/>
                        <p>The deliberation of the Parliament during the present session will be
                            directed to a solution of the question of the annexation of the Kongo to
                            Belgium, and this important measure will take precedence of all
                            others.</p>
                        <p>The proceedings of Parliament will be observed with interest and reported
                            to the department from time to time.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Henry Lane
                            Wilson</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>